---
const boundaryPoints = [
  "We do not process payments.",
  "We do not need full card data.",
  "We do not replace your ERP or accounting system.",
  "We only need the fields required for workflow state, matching, reconciliation, approvals, and auditability.",
  "We prefer scoped credentials and least-privilege access.",
  "Sensitive workflow actions should be logged with actor, timestamp, reason, and outcome."
];
---
<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 mb-8 reveal">
  <div class="bg-surface/50 dark:bg-stone-950 rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 shadow-sm relative overflow-hidden">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary dark:text-stone-50 mb-4 relative z-10">
      Data boundaries
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-stone-400 mb-8 relative z-10">
      We design early workflow slices to avoid unnecessary data exposure.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm text-primary dark:text-stone-300 font-semibold mb-5 relative z-10">
      For finance and AR workflows, that usually means:
    </p>
    <ul class="space-y-5 relative z-10">
      {boundaryPoints.map(point => (
        <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-600 mt-2 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span class="text-sm text-primary dark:text-stone-300 leading-relaxed">{point}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 relative z-10">
      In AR collections workflows, the first slice can often work with customer identifiers, invoice references, aging data, receipt/payment references, dispute states, owner mapping, and workflow notes—not broad access to every finance table.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
